Fix allowlist add: idempotent on duplicates, graceful on invalid, with feedback

Root cause: addAllowedEmail did a raw insert and threw on any error with no
user feedback. The email column is unique, so re-adding an already-listed
email raised 23505 and crashed the action, reading as "nothing was added"
(every name the team re-added was already on the list). A successful add also
gave no confirmation.

Fix: validate with safeParse (invalid gives a notice, not a crash); catch
23505 and treat an existing email as success (idempotent); redirect back to
/settings with an added / already-listed / invalid notice banner. Verified
against the live DB: table writable, duplicate raises 23505.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
